File: Off switch Paul Cross/Flickr JOHANNESBURG - A bleak Valentine's Day is in store for some Tshwane residents. The City has cut off power supply to the Flamingo Adult Entertainment Club because of unpaid bills. Tshwane has been disconnecting the power to numerous buildings in the city. READ: SA's electricity crisis | Tshwane on disconnection drive Tshwane's debtor's book currently stands at around R17-billion. Services have already been cut off at the Sheraton Hotel near the Union Buildings and some shopping centres. Flamingo was shut off because of an illegal connection, they owe about R621,000 from R1.2-million billed to their neighbour.